            "text": "Joule per gram per kelvin per cubic meter is a composed unit with factor units J^1 · g^-1 · K^-1 · m^-3. It measures specific heat per unit volume using gram as the mass unit. This unit results from the original prefixed unit by removing the 'Kilo' prefix from the mass factor. Numerically, 1 J/(g·K·m³) = 1000 J/(kg·K·m³).",
